Total Successful Journeys (GOV.UK One Login only, not Doc Checking App)
tiles.customName: Total Successful Journeys (GOV.UK One Login only, not Doc Checking App)

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
## Successful Journeys

Successful Sign Ins shows both the success for `new` and `existing` accounts.

Total Successful Journeys Show. the number of completed journeys where a user has gone through all steps and been returned to the service (RP).

The Journey Breakdown splits the total successful journeys by journey type of user creating an account and user signing into an existing account. It also shows users using the document checking app who did not need to create an account or sign in.

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
## Accounts

No of accounts where user has verified their 2FA method (either verified their phone number or completed auth app registration).

New accounts per day is taking the difference in the No of verified accounts per day to calculate new verified accounts.

The request to /authorize shows the number of users making a login request

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
## Successful Journeys detailed breakdown

Splitting down the successfully  journeys even further by the multi-factor authentication type used and the multi-factor authentication requirement. If the service required 2FA or 1FA.

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
## Journey Breakdown

Number of journeys completed broken down by the requested level of confidence. Where
- Authentication only (P0)
- Identity Proofing and Verification (P2)
- Journey using Doc Checking app

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown:
## Authentication Success

Number of journeys where user has reached the requested level of credential trust, i.e. successfully verified their password (for a 1FA journey) or verified their password AND passed the 2FA check (for a 2FA journey).
